                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/110.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires at
                            Panama</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department’s August 11. Ex-President Leguía of Peru arrived yesterday. I have
                    informed Canal Zone authorities. Met and escorted Leguía to hotel. He expects to
                    remain about two weeks, sailing via Jamaica for New York and Europe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
